Two-Thirds of London ‘Boris Bikes’ Need Repair, Independent Says

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-02-20T11:24:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/two-thirds-of-london-boris-bikes-need-repair-independent-says.html
Two-thirds of the 5,400 London
cycle-hire bicycles, a project initiated by London Mayor  Boris Johnson , have had to be mended, the  Independent on Sunday
reported , citing a U.K. Freedom of Information disclosure.  Up to 3,566 bikes have been repaired in the first six
months since their July introduction, with an average of 181
bikes out of  service  at any one time, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in London at 
